    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-11-01T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-11-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="857"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d857">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.03/11–150: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Yugoslavia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-11-01T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 1, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>323. Secy today handed Popovic fol reply his note Oct 20<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d857fn1">Regarding the Yugoslav note under reference here, see
                        footnote 2, <ref target="#pg_1474">p. 1474</ref>.</note>:</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“The Govt of the US has carefully studied the available info regarding the
                        consequences of the drought and wishes to inform you of its desire to extend
                        assistance to the Yugo people in the present emergency.</p>
                    <p>“The Govt of the US recognizes the importance of commencing food shipments
                        this month and of having minimum stocks available in Yugo by the end of the
                        year in order to prevent human suffering during the coming winter. I am
                        pleased to inform you that the Govt of the US is prepared to take measures
                        which are immed available to provide foodstuffs for this purpose. It is
                        understood that the Govts of the US and of Yugo will agree promptly on
                        appropriate arrangements covering matters such as supply and transportation,
                        equitable distribution of the foodstuffs to the population of Yugo, and
                        public awareness of this assistance.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Secy indicated that shortly Dept wld be in touch with Yugo <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> re details and methods for providing food which
                    involve several agencies US Govt. Secy also indicated in addition this stop-gap
                    program Congress when it reconvenes will be requested for funds with which
                    continue program. When Popovic asked in what manner Yugo Govt cld contribute
                    smoothing way for favorable Congressional action Secy replied Dept wld consider
                    this helpful suggestion and discuss it with Amb later.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
